### Task #6 - Partitioning in MySQL ##

Partitioning allows data storage of large datasets into multiple smaller partitions while keeping them together as one table. It also helps improve performance by reducing I/O operations required during queries. This feature is available from version 8+ of MySql.
In this assignment we will learn how partitioning works along with its pros & cons. We will then create our own customized partitioned table using two different methods i.e. Hash Partitions and Range Partitions respectively. In both cases, we'll see how these types of partitioning affects performance when used on a larger dataset.
